# Scenario: SEARCHING NEVER REGISTERS — Quectel BG95-M3 attempting NB-IoT (Cat-NB1)
# in a rural deployment with sparse NB-IoT coverage. Modem cycles through scan but
# never registers.
# Key signals:
#   +QCFG: "iotopmode",1     (NB-IoT only — Cat-M is disabled)
#   +CSQ: 9,99               (very weak)
#   +QCSQ: NBIOT, RSRP -118  (at the edge of NB1 sensitivity, ~-120 dBm)
#   +CEREG: 2,2,,,,          (searching, never reaches 1 or 5)
#   +CGATT: 0
# Diagnosis: device is RAT-locked to NB-IoT but local towers offer Cat-M1, OR
# the NB-IoT signal is below usable threshold. NB-IoT propagates further than Cat-M
# but requires a tower that explicitly broadcasts NB1.
# Customer guidance:
